  "text": "An important overarching generalization is that it is reasonable to expect that the first year of implementation will be a learning year where all targets may not be achieved. Indeed, out of the six FBP sites, only one site met its objectives in all four of the outcome areas we SUCCESSFUL HOME VISITING START-UP 29 examined. The sites were different in terms of key contextual factors related to the implementation outcomes. These include factors such as the available workforce, the geographic size of their catchment area, and the degree to which the infrastructure of their host organization provided support. The FBP curricula and the replication guide provided a great deal of structure for the home visits, but aspects of the program operations outside of home visits were subject to more uncertainties. Hence, in the first year, the sites negotiated these aspects by developing systems and networks that could contribute to successful program implementation in future years. These findings are consistent with those of [CITATION_1] , who suggest that full program implementation through all the six stages presented in Figure 1 is likely to take three years.",
